  output: # Sorting repeated blocks

Use this when a sheet contains multiple independent table-like blocks separated by blank rows and each block may begin with an in-band header row.

```python
from openpyxl import load_workbook

wb = load_workbook("input.xlsx")
ws = wb["Sheet1"]

