  output: # Formula-safe text predicates for aggregate formulas

Use this when a workbook formula must aggregate rows whose text both includes one pattern and excludes another, especially when digit exclusion must be evaluated safely for each cell rather than through fragile nested arrays.

```python
from openpyxl import load_workbook

wb = load_workbook("input.xlsx")
